<BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James           
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B49C002.htm'>Ephesians 2</A></P><CENTER><H2             
ALIGN=CENTER>The Epistle of Paul to the Ephesians</H2></CENTER><P><A            
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 3</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>For this cause I Paul, the prisoner 
of YAHSHUA MASHIYACH for you Gentiles,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>If ye have heard of the dispensation of the grace 
of ELOHIYM which is given me to you-ward:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>How that by revelation he made known unto me the  
mystery; (as I wrote afore in few words,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A     
NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>Whereby, when ye read, ye may understand my       
knowledge in the mystery of MASHIYACH)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Which in other ages was not made known unto the   
sons of men, as it is now revealed unto his holy apostles and prophets by the   
Spirit;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>That   
the Gentiles should be fellowheirs, and of the same body, and partakers of his  
promise in MASHIYACH by the gospel:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7> 
<H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Whereof I was made a minister, according to the gift of   
the grace of ELOHIYM given unto me by the effectual working of his power.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>Unto me, who am   
less than the least of all saints, is this grace given, that I should preach    
among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of MASHIYACH;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>And to make all men see what is the 
fellowship of the mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid  
in ELOHIYM, who created all things by YAHSHUA MASHIYACH:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>To the intent that now unto the   
principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known by the church the   
manifold wisdom of ELOHIYM,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>    
11</H4></TD><TD><P>According to the eternal purpose which he purposed in        
MASHIYACH YAHSHUA our ADONAY:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>  
12</H4></TD><TD><P>In whom we have boldness and access with confidence by the   
faith of him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>Wherefore I desire that ye faint not at my tribulations for you, which is    
your glory.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P> 
For this cause I bow my knees unto the Father of our ADONAY YAHSHUA             
MASHIYACH,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>  
Of whom the whole family in heaven and earth is named,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>That he would grant you,          
according to the riches of his glory, to be strengthened with might by his      
Spirit in the inner man;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4>
</TD><TD><P>That MASHIYACH may dwell in your hearts by faith; that ye, being    
rooted and grounded in love,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>   
18</H4></TD><TD><P>May be able to comprehend with all saints what is the        
breadth, and length, and depth, and height;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>And to know the love of MASHIYACH, which        
passeth knowledge, that ye might be filled with all the fulness of ELOHIYM.</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>Now unto him    
that is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think,         
according to the power that worketh in us,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Unto him be glory in the church by MASHIYACH    
YAHSHUA throughout all ages, world without end. Amen.</P></TD></TR></TABLE>     
